<denchmark-link:https://github.com/rohrl>@rohrl</denchmark-link> OK, I figured it out. Keras <denchmark-link:https://keras.io/layers/core/#merge>merge layers</denchmark-link> have a field that determines how to merge the layers, whether via concatenation or summation, etc. Currently, we've been directly mapping Keras merge layers to DL4J Merge vertices, but when the mode is something other than concat (e.g., sum), we should map it to a DL4J ElementWiseVertex. Will fix before next release and post an update here once done.
